WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.350 --> 00:00:04.496
NULL:  Every gap, every shortcut, every forgotten door -

2
00:00:04.496 --> 00:00:05.765
I will find it.

3
00:00:06.065 --> 00:00:08.617
VEGA:  Not tonight. Even if you slip in, you

4
00:00:08.617 --> 00:00:10.065
will not move unseen.

5
00:00:10.365 --> 00:00:12.507
NOVA:  Because someone's watching?

6
00:00:12.807 --> 00:00:15.967
VEGA:  Because the watchtowers never sleep.

7
00:00:17.017 --> 00:00:20.632
NULL:  I slipped a careless credential past your wall.

8
00:00:20.632 --> 00:00:22.632
Now I move in the shadows.

9
00:00:22.932 --> 00:00:26.292
VEGA:  Shadows don't last here. The watchtowers never sleep.

10
00:00:27.342 --> 00:00:30.247
VEGA:  Layer two assumes someone got in. Now we

11
00:00:30.247 --> 00:00:32.862
see them, stop the rot, and respond.

12
00:00:33.162 --> 00:00:37.628
Three families keep watch: Audit, System Integrity, and

13
00:00:37.628 --> 00:00:39.090
Incident Response.

14
00:00:40.140 --> 00:00:43.232
NOVA:  AU, SI, and IR. The eyes, the immune

15
00:00:43.232 --> 00:00:45.722
system, and the firefighters.

16
00:00:46.772 --> 00:00:49.532
VEGA:  The Chronicler, Audit and Accountability.

17
00:00:49.832 --> 00:00:52.712
VEGA:  It records every footstep, so no deed goes

18
00:00:52.712 --> 00:00:53.192
unseen.

19
00:00:53.492 --> 00:00:56.904
VEGA:  In reality, that's logging security-relevant events so you

20
00:00:56.904 --> 00:00:59.492
can review them and hold people accountable.

21
00:01:00.542 --> 00:01:02.724
NOVA:  What exactly is a 'log'?

22
00:01:03.024 --> 00:01:05.980
VEGA:  A diary the system keeps. A Windows Event

23
00:01:05.980 --> 00:01:08.503
Log, a syslog, a tool like Splunk -

24
00:01:08.503 --> 00:01:09.224
same idea.

25
00:01:10.274 --> 00:01:12.834
VEGA:  AU-2 chooses what's worth logging.

26
00:01:13.134 --> 00:01:15.050
NULL:  So I'll just delete the logs when I'm

27
00:01:15.050 --> 00:01:15.309
done.

28
00:01:16.774 --> 00:01:20.534
VEGA:  Not so fast. AU-9 protects the logs themselves.

29
00:01:20.834 --> 00:01:23.696
NOVA:  So the Null can't quietly rewrite history.

30
00:01:24.746 --> 00:01:27.474
ARCHIVIST:  Identify the types of events that the system

31
00:01:27.474 --> 00:01:29.892
is capable of logging in support of the

32
00:01:29.892 --> 00:01:30.822
audit function:

33
00:01:31.872 --> 00:01:33.742
VEGA:  A log no one reads, or one that

34
00:01:33.742 --> 00:01:35.672
can be erased, is no log at all.

35
00:01:42.172 --> 00:01:45.465
VEGA:  The Chronicler's oath. Every footstep written; no page

36
00:01:45.465 --> 00:01:45.892
erased.

37
00:01:46.942 --> 00:01:49.902
VEGA:  The Healer, System and Information Integrity.

38
00:01:50.202 --> 00:01:53.206
NOVA:  It finds the rot, cures the sickness, and

39
00:01:53.206 --> 00:01:54.744
keeps the truth true.

40
00:01:55.044 --> 00:01:58.499
VEGA:  In reality, that's patching flaws, blocking malicious code,

41
00:01:58.499 --> 00:02:02.071
monitoring for intrusions, and verifying nothing was tampered

42
00:02:02.071 --> 00:02:02.364
with.

43
00:02:03.414 --> 00:02:07.614
VEGA:  SI-2 is flaw remediation, the discipline of patching.

44
00:02:09.914 --> 00:02:12.591
VEGA:  And SI-4 watches the system for signs of

45
00:02:12.591 --> 00:02:13.394
an intruder.

46
00:02:13.694 --> 00:02:17.367
NULL:  Every move I make... another tower turns my

47
00:02:17.367 --> 00:02:17.709
way.

48
00:02:18.759 --> 00:02:22.144
NULL:  Six days I moved in your shadows before

49
00:02:22.144 --> 00:02:24.054
a single tower turned.

50
00:02:24.354 --> 00:02:25.136
NOVA:  Six days?!

51
00:02:25.436 --> 00:02:27.976
VEGA:  Six days - but SI-4 saw the anomaly,

52
00:02:27.976 --> 00:02:30.587
and AU-9 kept the logs he tripped. He

53
00:02:30.587 --> 00:02:32.916
got in. He did not get out clean.

54
00:02:33.216 --> 00:02:35.911
NULL:  ...this time.

55
00:02:36.961 --> 00:02:41.317
ARCHIVIST:  Identify, report, and correct system flaws;

56
00:02:42.367 --> 00:02:45.447
VEGA:  Integrity is keeping the system clean and honest.

57
00:02:52.667 --> 00:02:55.052
VEGA:  The Healer's oath. Find the rot, close the

58
00:02:55.052 --> 00:02:56.187
wound, keep it true.

59
00:02:57.237 --> 00:02:59.357
VEGA:  The Firewatch, Incident Response.

60
00:02:59.657 --> 00:03:02.329
VEGA:  When something burns, it sounds the alarm and

61
00:03:02.329 --> 00:03:03.457
contains the blaze.

62
00:03:03.757 --> 00:03:08.145
VEGA:  In reality, that's detecting, reporting, analyzing, containing, and

63
00:03:08.145 --> 00:03:10.437
recovering from security incidents.

64
00:03:11.487 --> 00:03:14.069
NOVA:  When does a threat become an 'incident'?

65
00:03:14.369 --> 00:03:17.328
VEGA:  The moment it stops being hypothetical - malware

66
00:03:17.328 --> 00:03:19.609
runs, data leaks, a system goes down.

67
00:03:20.659 --> 00:03:23.241
NOVA:  What happens the moment we spot the Null?

68
00:03:23.541 --> 00:03:27.178
VEGA:  IR-4 takes over, handling the incident end to

69
00:03:27.178 --> 00:03:27.501
end.

70
00:03:28.551 --> 00:03:33.613
VEGA:  Every incident follows a rhythm: prepare, detect, contain,

71
00:03:33.613 --> 00:03:35.271
eradicate, recover.

72
00:03:35.571 --> 00:03:38.960
NOVA:  And IR-8 writes the plan that makes it

73
00:03:38.960 --> 00:03:39.673
routine.

74
00:03:40.723 --> 00:03:44.751
ARCHIVIST:  Implement an incident handling capability for incidents that

75
00:03:44.751 --> 00:03:48.040
is consistent with the incident response plan and

76
00:03:48.040 --> 00:03:53.075
includes preparation, detection and analysis, containment, eradication, and

77
00:03:53.075 --> 00:03:53.679
recovery;

78
00:03:54.729 --> 00:03:57.689
VEGA:  The best responders practiced before the fire.

79
00:04:05.029 --> 00:04:07.682
VEGA:  The Firewatch's oath. When it burns, we are

80
00:04:07.682 --> 00:04:08.669
already running.

81
00:04:09.719 --> 00:04:13.237
VEGA:  Selecting and implementing was the wall. Watching is

82
00:04:13.237 --> 00:04:14.319
how you keep it.

83
00:04:18.319 --> 00:04:22.384
NOVA:  Scenario: the Null deletes logs. What stops it?

84
00:04:22.384 --> 00:04:23.941
Pause, and answer.

85
00:04:30.991 --> 00:04:32.271
VEGA:  The answer is B.

86
00:04:34.591 --> 00:04:36.631
VEGA:  And who runs toward the fire?

87
00:04:43.681 --> 00:04:45.241
VEGA:  The answer is A.

88
00:04:47.281 --> 00:04:50.265
NOVA:  Notebook: assume they got in, then see them,

89
00:04:50.265 --> 00:04:52.503
heal the system, and answer fast.

90
00:04:52.803 --> 00:04:56.083
VEGA:  Seen, healed, and answered. The towers hold.

91
00:04:56.383 --> 00:04:59.158
NULL:  Then I'll turn your own people against you.

92
00:04:59.458 --> 00:05:01.515
VEGA:  Then we ride to the Keepers of the

93
00:05:01.515 --> 00:05:01.818
Pact.
